            "answer_text": "If you want to insert a URL (\"http://.....\") then you just copy from your browser bar and paste into gmail. You can do that even on your phone.  If you want to insert a link with a URL behind it, (the \"LINK WORDS\" show up in color and you click on them to activate the URL) then you need the full desktop version and need to write your message in HTML rather than plain text. ",
